div.p:
The East, as it followes in the Evangelist, was the place of the Starres first appearing that where sinne abounded grace might superabound. There Sorcerers, and Practisers of hellish Arts serv'd Satan, and thence shin'd a spirituall light to chase away darke ignorance, and spirituall wickednesse. In lumine tuo ridebunt lumen. In thy light they shall see light saith David;
               S. Austen.
               In Christo tuo videbunt gratiam. In the Lords Christ, or Gods Anoynted they shall apprehend grace to be made partakers of the inheritance of the Saints in Light, who hath taken them out of the Kingdome of darknesse, and translated them into the Kingdome of his deare Sonne. So true is that of Esay, the people of the Gentills, which sate in darknesse saw a great light, and light is risen to them, which dwell in the region of the shadow of death.
